One Ebulus Buku has reportedly been hospitalized in Warri, Delta State after he was allegedly attacked and shot by suspected cultists in Ovwian community in Udu Local Government Area. The victim was shot on the head and legs before he was dispossessed of his mobile phone, money and other personal effects by the rampaging cultists, DAILY POST can report. The victim’s family has now urged the Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali to investigate the matter thoroughly with a view to arresting and prosecuting culprits involved in the dastardly acts. Ebulus Buku is an Ijaw Youth leader in Delta State. Police vow to arrest cultists who killed, used victim’s head to play football